 introduction, which contextualizes and outlines Jankélévitch's reading of Bergson, additional essays on Bergson by Jankélévitch, and Bergson's letters to Jankélévitch.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 12. Dez 2020) 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh1 aLefebvre, Alexandre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLefebvre, Alexandre, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchott, Nils F.1 aSchott, Nils F., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDUK eBook-Package 2014-2015z978311071182040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822375333zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822375333423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780822375333.jpg  a978-3-11-071182-0  DUK eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles